description:
The time of the end of collection of the data in the ping,
in local time and with minute precision, including timezone information.
This is also the time this ping was generated
and is likely well before ping transmission time.
name: end_time

annotation.content:
This ends up being a string in the data and is not easily parsed into a `DATE` or `TIMESTAMP`, thus there is a 
pre-parsed version that is much easier to use `ping_info.parsed_end_time` when writing queries.
